May (; , Maay) is a rural locality (a selo), one of two settlements, in addition to Berdigestyakh, in Berdigestyakhsky Rural Okrug of Gorny District in the Sakha Republic, Russia. It is located  from Berdigestyakh, the administrative center of the district. Its population as of the 2010 Census was 10, of whom 5 were male and 5 female, down from 13 as recorded during the 2002 Census.
